10/07/2015

Disclosure in accordance with the Law of 2 May 2007




Regulated information
 
 LEUVEN – Belgium – July 10, 2015 – Option NV discloses the information required under article 15, § 1 and article 18, § 1 of the Law of 2 May 2007 regarding the disclosure of important shareholdings in listed companies.
Information per June 18, 2015:

Total share capital: EUR 4,844,802.70
Total number of voting securities: 96,896,054
Total number of voting rights (= the denominator): 96,896,05

 
More details are available on Option’s website: http://www.option.com/about_sub_pages/capital-structure-uk
 
According to Option’s bylaws, the threshold as from which a shareholding needs to be disclosed, has been set at 3%. 

10/07/2015

Mededeling conform de bepalingen van de wet van 2 mei 2007




Gereglementeerde informatie
 
LEUVEN, België – 10 juli 2015 – Option NV publiceert de informatie zoals vereist in artikel 15, § 1 van de Wet van 2 mei 2007 op de openbaarmaking van belangrijke deelnemingen in beursgenoteerde bedrijven. 
Informatie per 18 juni 2015:

Totaal maatschappelijk kapitaal: 4.844.802,70
Totaal aantal stemrechtverlenende effecten: 96.896.054
Totaal aantal stemrechten (= de noemer): 96.896.054 

 
Meer details zijn beschikbaar op de website van Option:
http://www.option.com/about_sub_pages/capital-structure-nl
 
Overeenkomstig Option’s statuten, werd de drempel vanaf dewelke een deelneming moet worden bekendgemaakt, vastgesteld op 3 %. 

03/07/2015

Regulated information: financial update




LEUVEN – Belgium – July 3, 2015 – Following the continued review by the statutory auditor of the Company of the cash position of the Company and its continuity, the Board of Directors has further deliberated in this respect and resolved to inform the market about the reasons why the continuity can, in its opinion, be maintained. The Company therefore wishes to provide the market with an update in relation to its financial situation and possible strategic options.   
In the first half year the Company active in the pioneering market of IoT (Internet of Things) faced postponed sales and as a consequence important orders shifted to the second half of the year. However the Company’s partners maintain their outlook for 2015. Although the second quarter was stronger than the first, this has resulted in a half year turnover that is well below the company’s own expectations.
Through rigorous cash management the Company has been able to keep its cash position under control thanks to the bridge financing (as announced on April 21, 2015), by accelerating customer payments, by optimizing the supply chain and by further reducing the operational costs.
To further improve the Company’s cash position, to ensure and improve the Company’s market position and to secure future growth, the Company started up confidential discussions in order to engage with a number of financial and industrial partners. 

